    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of blanc de Chine porcelain ware, which is fine white translucent porcelain with a thick white glaze.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045361/Savage and Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Ceramics (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fijn wit doorschijnend porselein met dik wit glazuur, gemaakt in Dehua (Te Hua) in de late Ming-periode en sinds de 18e eeuw geëxporteerd naar Zuidoost-Azië en Europa. Karakteristieke vormen waren kleine figuren die boeddhistische goden en hoogwaardigheidsbekleders voorstelden, bekers en vazen. De stijl werd geïmiteerd in Saint-Cloud in Frankrijk en in Engeland in Chelsea en Bow.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>晚明時代德化生產的細瓷，潔白剔透並有著厚重的白釉，十八世紀開始外銷至東南亞及歐洲。最有特色的樣式為刻畫小佛像、顯貴人物、杯子、花瓶等。法國聖克盧 (Saint-Cloud)、英國雀兒喜 (Chelsea)和博屋 (Bow) 等地亦模仿此風格。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
